  "texts": [
    "Thus, M, x ⊩ □ i p or M, x ⊩ □ i q.For part 3, suppose M, x ⊩ □ j (□ i p ∨ □ i q).",
    "If R j (x) is empty, then M, x ⊩ □ j φ for every φ ∈ L(Φ, I), so we are done.",
    "If R j (x) is nonempty, then by R-max it has a maximum f j (x), in which case M, x ⊩ □ j (□ i p∨□ i q) (iii) (■ i X) ≃ = ■ ≃ i X ≃.",
    "Checking (i) is straightforward.",
    "For (ii), from right to left, if [z] ≃ ̸ ∈ (X ⊃ Y) ≃, so z ̸ ∈ X ⊃ Y, then there is a z ′ ⊑ z such that z ′ ∈ X but z ′ ̸ ∈ Y, which implies[z ′] ≃ ⊑ ≃ [z] ≃ and [z ′] ≃ ∈ X ≃ but [z ′] ≃ ̸ ∈ Y ≃, so [z] ≃ ̸ ∈ X ≃ ⊃ ≃ Y ≃."
